condition.narrative: Finance Agreement: Project Management Team | Description: Schedule 2 Section I.A.3.: The Borrower shall maintain until completionof the Project a Project management team (the PMT) with functions and responsibilities acceptable to the Bank, including adequateresources and assisted by professional and administrative staff, all in numbers and with terms of reference and qualifications andexperience acceptable to the Bank, including a Project coordinator. | Frequency: CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement: Safeguards | Description: Schedule 2 Section I.D.: The Borrower, through DNP, shall adopt terms of reference fornon-consulting services and for consultant services under the Project in accordance with the requirements of the Bank SafeguardsPolicies then in force and as applicable, align in a manner satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency: CONTINUOUS

title.narrative: Level of automation of administrative and financial processes

target.value: At least 210 beneficiary subnational governments have increased their automation level by 10 points based on the Digital GovernmentIndex - MIPG Indicator I20.

title.narrative: Intermediate Result indicator 3.1: Territorial Management Model (TMM) design.

baseline.value: No design of the Territorial Management Model is place

target.value: Design of the Territorial Management Model (TMM) has been completed, including the definition of technical specifications andimplementation strategy.

actual.value: Design of the Territorial Management Model (TMM) has been completed, including the definition of technical specifications andimplementation strategy.

title.narrative: Intermediate Result indicator 4.2: Design of instruments for territorial management control.

actual.value: Control model has been integrated in the functional requirements for the financial and revenue management module of the TMM

title.narrative: Intermediate Result indicator 3.3: Provision of Technical Assistance to Subnational Governments

baseline.value: No technical assistance on the functionalities of the TMM has yet been provided.

target.value: 300 municipalities have received technical assistance as part of the TMM.

actual.value: The NPD has provided technical assistance to 365 municipalities in the planning and monitoring modules of the TMM, including 40pilot municipalities where the financial and revenue management module has been implemented.

title.narrative: Intermediate Result indicator 3.4: Technical assistance to strengthen citizen participation along the public management cycle.

baseline.value: No tools or methodologies exist to support citizen participation.

target.value: A citizen participation toolkit has been designed and implemented by at least 50 municipal governments.

actual.value: The NPD has developed a methodology to streamline citizen participation in the planning process of public investment projects,which has been embedded in the territorial kit and implemented in 300 beneficiary municipal governments.

title.narrative: Intermediate Result indicator 3.2: Implementation of the Territorial Management Model (TMM)

baseline.value: TMM has noy yet been implemented

target.value: TMM has been implemented in at least 280 municipal governments.

actual.value: The TMM has been implemented in a pilot group of 40 municipalities

title.narrative: Intermediate Result indicator 1.1: Formulation of modern spatially integrated territorial development plans (POT)
Intermediate Result indicator 1.2: Implementation of multi-purpose land cadaster pilot

baseline.value: The multi-purpose land cadaster has not been piloted in any municipality.

target.value: Pilots have been implemented in 7 municipalities

actual.value: Pilots have been implemented in 7 municipalities

title.narrative: Indicator 1.3: Development and implementation of a support platform to formulate Territorial Land Use Plans

baseline.value: Beta version of the platform has been completed but has not yet been officially launched

target.value: At least 60 subnational governments have used the platform to formulate Land Use Plans.

actual.value: The platform to formulate Land Use Plans is used by 64 municipal governments.

title.narrative: Percentage of beneficiary municipalities with an improved management score in the Municipal Performance Measure (MDM) index

target.value: 50% of beneficiary municipalities have improved their score in the management component of the MDM index by at least 10 points

title.narrative: Percentage of beneficiary Subnational entities using instruments developed by the project to strengthen the decentralization framework and public management
Percentage of beneficiary municipalities with updated long term planning instruments
Intermediate Result indicator 1.4: Formulation of Regional Land Use Plans (MOTR) and Regional Strategic Plans (PER)

baseline.value: No MOTR and PER have yet been formulated.

target.value: MOTR and PER have been formulated for at least 4 regions.

actual.value: No MORT and PER have yet been formulated.
